HEADWORD: Tachyscope
<hw>Tach"y*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>tachy`s</grk> quick + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>An early form
of animated-picture machine, devised in 1889 by <person>Otto
Ansch⟦uum⟧tz</person> of <city>Berlin</city>, in which the
chronophotographs were mounted upon the periphery of a rotating
wheel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

